From 1e9171f1bdf6ea9d8b87ed1a18bd068327251b7b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Hadar Sivan <hsivan@nvidia.com>
Date: Sun, 2 Feb 2025 12:09:34 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Add support for global resource allocation via external
 server communication

This commit introduces the select_gnl_cons_tres.so plugin, which checks
whether a job can be allocated a global resource, such as power, by
communicating with an external server that monitors this resource.
Key changes:
- The modified plugin is built under the new name select_gnl_cons_tres.so,
where the name stands for global and local consumable trackable resources.
- After cloning the vanilla Slurm repository, it is recommended to copy
the cons_tres folder to cons_tres_org and apply the patch that adds
global resource (globres) support. After applying the patch, compiling
will produce both the original select_cons_tres.so and the modified
select_gnl_cons_tres.so.

Note: this change includes a temporary workaround to enable gnl_cons_tres
Select plugin.
We use the SELECT_PLUGIN_CONS_RES plugin ID (formerly for cons_res,
which is no longer in use) for gnl_cons_tres.
This is a temporary solution. In the future, once this code is merged
into the official SchedMD codebase, it will become part of the
cons_tres plugin.
